Here are the most commonly used Windows Command Prompt (CMD) commands:

{
  New-Item a.cpp              // creates a new a.cpp file
  mkdir fold                 // creates a folder named fold

  for running file:
  PS C:\Users\Lenovo\Desktop\C-C++ Practice\y> g++ .\x.cpp
  PS C:\Users\Lenovo\Desktop\C-C++ Practice\y> .\a.exe 

  
}








1. File and Directory Management
dir: Lists files and directories in the current directory.

Example: dir
cd: Changes the current directory.

Example: cd C:\path\to\directory
pwd: Prints the current directory (Not native in CMD, but can be used in PowerShell).

mkdir: Creates a new directory.

Example: mkdir new_directory
rmdir: Removes an empty directory.

Example: rmdir directory_name
del: Deletes files.

Example: del file.txt
copy: Copies files from one location to another.

Example: copy file1.txt D:\backup\
move: Moves or renames files or directories.

Example: move file1.txt D:\new_location\
2. Viewing and Managing Files
type: Displays the contents of a file.
Example: type file.txt
more: Displays a file's content one page at a time.
Example: more file.txt
cls: Clears the screen.
Example: cls
3. System Information
systeminfo: Displays detailed system information.
Example: systeminfo
tasklist: Lists all currently running processes.
Example: tasklist
taskkill: Terminates a process by its PID (Process ID).
Example: taskkill /PID 1234
ipconfig: Displays network configuration information.
Example: ipconfig
4. Networking
ping: Sends packets to a network address to test connectivity.
Example: ping google.com
netstat: Displays active network connections.
Example: netstat -an
tracert: Traces the path of packets to a destination.
Example: tracert google.com
nslookup: Looks up DNS information for a domain.
Example: nslookup google.com
5. File Permissions
attrib: Displays or changes file attributes (e.g., hidden, read-only).
Example: attrib +h file.txt (sets the file as hidden)
6. User Management
net user: Displays user account information.
Example: net user username
net user username /add: Adds a new user.
Example: net user john /add
net localgroup: Displays or manages local group memberships.
Example: net localgroup administrators
7. Disk Management
chkdsk: Checks and repairs file system errors on a disk.

Example: chkdsk C:
diskpart: Manages disk partitions.

Example: diskpart
format: Formats a drive or partition.

Example: format D:
8. Power Management
shutdown: Shuts down or restarts the system.
Example: shutdown /s /t 0 (shuts down immediately)
exit: Closes the Command Prompt window.
Example: exit
9. Miscellaneous
echo: Displays a message or turns command echoing on/off.
Example: echo Hello World
set: Displays or sets environment variables.
Example: set PATH
cls: Clears the terminal screen.
Example: cls
10. File Compression
compress (in PowerShell): Compresses files.
Example: Compress-Archive -Path file1.txt -DestinationPath archive.zip
These are the essential Windows Command Prompt commands used for system administration, file management, and network troubleshooting.